	Custom VPCs and ELBs

Application load balancers are layer 7 load balancers

Classic load balancers are layer 4 load balancers

You need two public subnets if you want high availability 


NATs vs Bations

Bastions are used for administration

NAT instances are on their way out in favor of NAT gateway

NAT instance will be behind a security group
NAT gateway wont be behind a security group

Exam Tips - NAT vs Bastions

- A NAT is used to provide internet traffic to EC2 instances in private subnets
- A Bastion is used to securely administer EC2 instances(using SSH or RDP) in private subnets. 
	- In Australia we call them jump boxes.